As of the [[census]]<ref name="GR2">{{cite web |url=https://www.census.gov |publisher=[[United States Census Bureau]] |accessdate=January 31, 2008 |title=U.S. Census website }}</ref> of 2000, there were 762 people, 343 households, and 220 families residing in the town. The population density was {{convert|221.7|PD/sqmi|PD/km2|sp=us|adj=off}}. There were 402 housing units at an average density of {{convert|116.9|/sqmi|/km2|sp=us|adj=off}}. The racial makeup of the town was 99.61% [[Race (United States Census)|White]], 0.13% [[Race (United States Census)|Native American]], and 0.26% from two or more races. 0.66% of the population were [[Race (United States Census)|Hispanic]] or [[Race (United States Census)|Latino]] of any race.

There were 343 households, out of which 27.7% had children under the age of 18 living with them, 48.7% were [[Marriage|married couples]] living together, 12.2% had a female householder with no husband present, and 35.6% were non-families. 34.1% of all households were made up of individuals, and 16.0% had someone living alone who was 65 years of age or older. The average household size was 2.22 and the average family size was 2.81.

In the town, the population was spread out, with 22.7% under the age of 18, 7.2% from 18 to 24, 25.1% from 25 to 44, 25.5% from 45 to 64, and 19.6% who were 65 years of age or older. The median age was 41 years. For every 100 females, there were 91.5 males. For every 100 females age 18 and over, there were 85.8 males.

The median income for a household in the town was $18,224, and the median income for a family was $27,857. Males had a median income of $28,611 versus $15,703 for females. The [[per capita income]] for the town was $14,516. About 22.4% of families and 26.5% of the population were below the [[poverty line]], including 37.3% of those under age 18 and 27.0% of those age 65 or over.

